modemStatsEntry.description: This is the structure of entries in the modemStatsTable.

modemStatsSlot.name: modemStatsSlot
modemStatsSlot.description: The slot that contains this modem

modemStatsIOP.name: modemStatsIOP
modemStatsIOP.description: The IOP on the card that controls this modem

modemStatsDMM.name: modemStatsDMM
modemStatsDMM.description: The DMM on the card that contains this modem

modemStatsPack.name: modemStatsPack
modemStatsPack.description: The pack on the DMM that contains this modem

modemStatsModem.name: modemStatsModem
modemStatsModem.description: The modem's number on the pack

modemStatsCurrentSessionID.name: modemStatsCurrentSessionID
modemStatsCurrentSessionID.description: If active, the ID of the modem's session

modemStatsModemIndex.name: modemStatsModemIndex
modemStatsModemIndex.description: The modem number associated with this entry

modemStatsRPI.name: modemStatsRPI
modemStatsRPI.description: This modem's current rating (0..100). A modem's RPI reveals a modem's quality relative to other modems.

modemStatsTotalCalls.name: modemStatsTotalCalls
modemStatsTotalCalls.description: The total number of calls assigned to this modem

modemStatsConnectedCalls.name: modemStatsConnectedCalls
modemStatsConnectedCalls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has successfully negotiated a connection with the remote modem.

modemStatsLast32Calls.name: modemStatsLast32Calls
modemStatsLast32Calls.description: A bitmask indicating connection success (bit is set) or failure (bit is not set) on the last 32 calls. The lowest-order bit represents the most recent call, and the highest-order bit represents the oldest call.

modemStatsConnectedWin.name: modemStatsConnectedWin
modemStatsConnectedWin.description: The number of consecutive calls assigned to this modem that connected successfully. A value of 0 indicates that the last call did not connect successfully.

modemStatsConnectedLose.name: modemStatsConnectedLose
modemStatsConnectedLose.description: The number of consecutive calls assigned to this modem that did not connect successfully. A value of 0 indicates that the last call did connect successfully.

modemStatsAuthCalls.name: modemStatsAuthCalls
modemStatsAuthCalls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected, and which have proceeded to the authentication stage. This does not mean that authentication was successful, just that it was attempted.

modemStatsLast32Auth.name: modemStatsLast32Auth
modemStatsLast32Auth.description: A bitmask indicating connection success (bit is set) or failure (bit is not set) on the last 32 calls reaching the authentication stage. The lowest-order bit represents the most recent call, and the highest-order bit represents the oldest call.

modemStatsAuthWin.name: modemStatsAuthWin
modemStatsAuthWin.description: The number of consecutive calls assigned to this modem that connected and reached the authentication stage. A value of 0 indicates that the last call did not reach the authentication stage.

modemStatsAuthLose.name: modemStatsAuthLose
modemStatsAuthLose.description: The number of consecutive calls assigned to this modem that did not reach the authentication stage. A value of 0 indicates that the last call did reach the authentication stage.

modemStatsECCalls.name: modemStatsECCalls
modemStatsECCalls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated an error correction protocol.

modemStatsDCCalls.name: modemStatsDCCalls
modemStatsDCCalls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated a data compression protocol.

modemStatsK56Calls.name: modemStatsK56Calls
modemStatsK56Calls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated the K56 Flex modulation protocol.

modemStatsV90Calls.name: modemStatsV90Calls
modemStatsV90Calls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated the V.90 modulation protocol.

modemStatsV34Calls.name: modemStatsV34Calls
modemStatsV34Calls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated the V.34 modulation protocol.

modemStatsV32Calls.name: modemStatsV32Calls
modemStatsV32Calls.description: The total numer of calls on which this modem has connected and negotiated the V.32 or V.32bis modulation protocols.

modemStatsStatsSamples.name: modemStatsStatsSamples
modemStatsStatsSamples.description: The total numer of calls on which call statistics were obtained. These statistics include minimum and maximum speeds, retrains and renegotiations, etc.

modemStatsInitialTxSum.name: modemStatsInitialTxSum
modemStatsInitialTxSum.description: The sum of the initial transmit speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the ConnectedCalls value to obtain an average initial transmit speed.

modemStatsMinTxSum.name: modemStatsMinTxSum
modemStatsMinTxSum.description: The sum of the minimum transmit speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average minimum transmit speed.

modemStatsMaxTxSum.name: modemStatsMaxTxSum
modemStatsMaxTxSum.description: The sum of the maximum transmit speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average maximum transmit speed.

modemStatsFinalTxSum.name: modemStatsFinalTxSum
modemStatsFinalTxSum.description: The sum of the final transmit speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average final transmit speed.

modemStatsMinTxSpeed.name: modemStatsMinTxSpeed
modemStatsMinTxSpeed.description: The minimum transmit speed negotiated by this modem.

modemStatsMaxTxSpeed.name: modemStatsMaxTxSpeed
modemStatsMaxTxSpeed.description: The maximum transmit speed negotiated by this modem.

modemStatsInitialRxSum.name: modemStatsInitialRxSum
modemStatsInitialRxSum.description: The sum of the initial receive speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the ConnectedCalls value to obtain an average initial receive speed.

modemStatsMinRxSum.name: modemStatsMinRxSum
modemStatsMinRxSum.description: The sum of the minimum receive speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average minimum receive speed.

modemStatsMaxRxSum.name: modemStatsMaxRxSum
modemStatsMaxRxSum.description: The sum of the maximum receive speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average maximum receive speed.

modemStatsFinalRxSum.name: modemStatsFinalRxSum
modemStatsFinalRxSum.description: The sum of the final receive speeds on all calls for which call statistics were obtained. This number can be divided by the StatsSamples value to obtain an average final receive speed.

modemStatsMinRxSpeed.name: modemStatsMinRxSpeed
modemStatsMinRxSpeed.description: The minimum receive speed negotiated by this modem.

modemStatsMaxRxSpeed.name: modemStatsMaxRxSpeed
modemStatsMaxRxSpeed.description: The maximum receive speed negotiated by this modem.

modemStatsDownloadAttempts.name: modemStatsDownloadAttempts
modemStatsDownloadAttempts.description: Number of times code was downloaded to the modem's pack

modemStatsDownloadSuccesses.name: modemStatsDownloadSuccesses
modemStatsDownloadSuccesses.description: Number of times code downloaded succeeded

modemStatsResetFailures.name: modemStatsResetFailures
modemStatsResetFailures.description: Number of times the modem failed to respond to commands

modemStatsResetRevivals.name: modemStatsResetRevivals
modemStatsResetRevivals.description: Number of times the modem was revived from the non-responsive state

modemStatsPackCrashes.name: modemStatsPackCrashes
modemStatsPackCrashes.description: Number of times the modem's pack seems to have crashed

modemStatsPackRevivals.name: modemStatsPackRevivals
modemStatsPackRevivals.description: Number of times the modem's apparently-crashed pack was revived with a download

sessionCountersBootEra.name: sessionCountersBootEra
sessionCountersBootEra.description: A number identifying the boot era for this system. This number will be set to a unique value each time the system is rebooted. This variable will not change until the System Controller Card (SCC) is rebooted. When prepended to a session serial number, yields a session identifier which will be unique for this system for all time.

sessionStatusTable.name: sessionStatusTable
sessionStatusTable.description: This table describes both active and inactive sessions. The table contains all active sessions and the most recent inactive sessions, up to a combined total of SessionTableSize entries. This table is ordered by session serial number. As new entries are appended to the bottom of the table, the inactive entries with the oldest termination time get aged out from near the top of the table.

sessionStatusEntry.name: sessionStatusEntry
sessionStatusEntry.description: This is the structure of entries in the sessionStatusTable.

sessionStatusSessionID.name: sessionStatusSessionID
sessionStatusSessionID.description: The serial number of this session, a unique number for this boot era. When combined with the value of BootEra, provides a session number that is unique for the life of the system.

sessionStatusState.name: sessionStatusState
sessionStatusState.description: This variable indicates the state of this session.

sessionStatusPermanentFlag.name: sessionStatusPermanentFlag
sessionStatusPermanentFlag.description: This variable indicates whether this session is permanent(2), meaning a long-lasting locally administered session such as a Frame Relay PVC, or switched(1), meaning a short-lived session resulting from a switched call.

sessionStatusVpopId.name: sessionStatusVpopId
sessionStatusVpopId.description: The identifier of the VPOP (administrative Group) to which the session belongs. A value of 0 indicates the default VPOP.

sessionStatusName.name: sessionStatusName
sessionStatusName.description: The name of the connection peer for this session. During authentication of the session, this field may contain the name submitted by the peer. During this time, the value of timeOfService will be zero. When the value of timeOfService is nonzero, this field will contain a fully authenticated name.

sessionStatusRemoteIP.name: sessionStatusRemoteIP
sessionStatusRemoteIP.description: The connection peer's IP address. If the link is numbered, then this is the address assigned to the other end of the link. If the link is not numbered, this may be the single IP address of the peer. For PPP connections, this is the result of IPNCP negotiation.

sessionStatusRemoteIPMask.name: sessionStatusRemoteIPMask
sessionStatusRemoteIPMask.description: The connection peer's IP address mask, used in conjunction with remoteIP.

sessionStatusLocalIP.name: sessionStatusLocalIP
sessionStatusLocalIP.description: The local IP address for this session. If the link is numbered, then this is the address assigned to the local end of the link. If the link is not numbered, this may be the primary IP address of the system. For PPP connections, this is the result of IPNCP negotiation.

sessionStatusLocalIPMask.name: sessionStatusLocalIPMask
sessionStatusLocalIPMask.description: The local IP address mask for this session, used in conjunction with localIP.

sessionStatusLinkService.name: sessionStatusLinkService
sessionStatusLinkService.description: A description of which link technology is being used by the session.

sessionStatusServiceMode.name: sessionStatusServiceMode
sessionStatusServiceMode.description: A description of which session service is being used by the session.

sessionStatusStartTime.name: sessionStatusStartTime
sessionStatusStartTime.description: The time that this session began, in seconds since the system booted.

sessionStatusStopTime.name: sessionStatusStopTime
sessionStatusStopTime.description: The time that this session stopped, in seconds since the system booted. This variable is only meaningful for sessions having the state inactive(0).

sessionStatusTimeOfModemSync.name: sessionStatusTimeOfModemSync
sessionStatusTimeOfModemSync.description: The time at which the modem synchronization completed, in seconds since the system booted.

sessionStatusTimeOfService.name: sessionStatusTimeOfService
sessionStatusTimeOfService.description: The time that this session entered its first negotiated or configured service, in seconds since the system booted. For example, for a session with serviceMode PPP, the time at which LCP and IPCP negotiations completed and the session was ready to forward user data.

sessionStatusTerminatingComponent.name: sessionStatusTerminatingComponent
sessionStatusTerminatingComponent.description: The component which initiated termination of this session. In cases where there are multiple causes of session termination, only the first cause detected is reported. This variable is only meaningful for sessions having the state inactive(0).

sessionStatusTerminationCause.name: sessionStatusTerminationCause
sessionStatusTerminationCause.description: The cause which initiated termination of this session. In cases where there are multiple causes of session termination, only the first cause detected is reported. This variable is only meaningful for sessions having the state inactive(0).

sessionStatusLastComponent.name: sessionStatusLastComponent
sessionStatusLastComponent.description: The last component which was connected in this session.

sessionStatusLayer2Slot.name: sessionStatusLayer2Slot

sessionStatusOriginateMode.name: sessionStatusOriginateMode

sessionStatusOctetsOut.name: sessionStatusOctetsOut

sessionStatusPacketsOut.name: sessionStatusPacketsOut

sessionStatusPort.name: sessionStatusPort

sessionStatusTimeslot.name: sessionStatusTimeslot

sessionStatusLinkCount.name: sessionStatusLinkCount
sessionStatusLinkCount.description: The number of sessions sharing the same remote IP address as this session. After a session is terminated, this value will represent the number of sessions at the time of termination.

sessionStatusTxStartDataRate.name: sessionStatusTxStartDataRate
sessionStatusTxStartDataRate.description: The transmit DCE data rate for this session. In the case of modem sessions, this will be the DCE rate reported as a result of initial modem negotiation, and may not track rate chanes during the call. For ISDN sessions, this will be the actual data service rate of the call. For Frame Relay sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the Frame Relay Physical Interface, even though multiple sessions may be sharing that Physical Interface. For other sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the physical interface. In no case should this be interepreted as a Quality-of-Service guarantee, or as the current line utilization or effective bandwidth on the interface. Note also that in the case of PPP multilink, this specifies the rate of only this link in the bundle, and not the aggregate rate of all links in the bundle.

sessionStatusRxStartDataRate.name: sessionStatusRxStartDataRate
sessionStatusRxStartDataRate.description: The receive data rate for this session. In the case of modem sessions, this will be the DCE rate reported as a result of initial modem negotiation, and may not track rate chanes during the call. For ISDN sessions, this will be the actual data service rate of the call. For Frame Relay sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the Frame Relay Physical Interface, even though multiple sessions may be sharing that Physical Interface. For other sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the physical interface. In no case should this be interepreted as a Quality-of-Service guarantee, or as the current line utilization or effective bandwidth on the interface. Note also that in the case of PPP multilink, this specifies the rate of only this link in the bundle, and not the aggregate rate of all links in the bundle.

sessionStatusTxEndDataRate.name: sessionStatusTxEndDataRate
sessionStatusTxEndDataRate.description: The transmit data rate at the end of a modem session.

sessionStatusRxEndDataRate.name: sessionStatusRxEndDataRate

sessionStatusRxMinDataRate.name: sessionStatusRxMinDataRate
sessionStatusRxMinDataRate.description: The minimum receive data rate during a modem session.

sessionStatusRxMaxDataRate.name: sessionStatusRxMaxDataRate
sessionStatusRxMaxDataRate.description: The maximum receive data rate during a modem session.

For Frame Relay sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the Frame Relay Physical Interface, even though multiple sessions may be sharing that Physical Interface. In no case should this be interepreted as a Quality-of-Service guarantee, or as the current line utilization or effective bandwidth on the interface. Note also that in the case of PPP multilink, this specifies the rate of only this link in the bundle, and not the aggregate rate of all links in the bundle.

As new entries are inserted into the table, the inactive entries with the oldest termination time get aged out from the table.

sessionStatusHistoryEntry.name: sessionStatusHistoryEntry
sessionStatusHistoryEntry.description: This is the structure of entries in the sessionStatusHistoryTable.

sessionStatusHistoryIndex.name: sessionStatusHistoryIndex
sessionStatusHistoryIndex.description: An index into a ring buffer of the last 2000 sessions.

sessionStatusHistorySessionID.name: sessionStatusHistorySessionID
sessionStatusHistorySessionID.description: The serial number of this session, a unique number for this boot era. When combined with the value of BootEra, provides a session number that is unique for the life of the system.

sessionStatusHistoryState.name: sessionStatusHistoryState
sessionStatusHistoryState.description: This variable indicates the state of this session.

sessionStatusHistoryPermanentFlag.name: sessionStatusHistoryPermanentFlag
sessionStatusHistoryPermanentFlag.description: This variable indicates whether this session is permanent(2), meaning a long-lasting locally administered session such as a Frame Relay PVC, or switched(1), meaning a short-lived session resulting from a switched call.

sessionStatusHistoryVpopId.name: sessionStatusHistoryVpopId
sessionStatusHistoryVpopId.description: The identifier of the VPOP (administrative Group) to which the session belongs. A value of 0 indicates the default VPOP.

sessionStatusHistoryName.name: sessionStatusHistoryName
sessionStatusHistoryName.description: The name of the connection peer for this session. During authentication of the session, this field may contain the name submitted by the peer. During this time, the value of timeOfService will be zero. When the value of timeOfService is nonzero, this field will contain a fully authenticated name.

sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIP.name: sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIP
sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIP.description: The connection peer's IP address. If the link is numbered, then this is the address assigned to the other end of the link. If the link is not numbered, this may be the single IP address of the peer. For PPP connections, this is the result of IPNCP negotiation.

sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPMask.name: sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPMask
sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPMask.description: The connection peer's IP address mask, used in conjunction with remoteIP.

sessionStatusHistoryLocalIP.name: sessionStatusHistoryLocalIP
sessionStatusHistoryLocalIP.description: The local IP address for this session. If the link is numbered, then this is the address assigned to the local end of the link. If the link is not numbered, this may be the primary IP address of the system. For PPP connections, this is the result of IPNCP negotiation.

sessionStatusHistoryLocalIPMask.name: sessionStatusHistoryLocalIPMask
sessionStatusHistoryLocalIPMask.description: The local IP address mask for this session, used in conjunction with localIP.

sessionStatusHistoryLinkService.name: sessionStatusHistoryLinkService
sessionStatusHistoryLinkService.description: A description of which link technology is being used by the session.

sessionStatusHistoryServiceMode.name: sessionStatusHistoryServiceMode
sessionStatusHistoryServiceMode.description: A description of which session service is being used by the session.

sessionStatusHistoryStartTime.name: sessionStatusHistoryStartTime
sessionStatusHistoryStartTime.description: The time that this session began, in seconds since the system booted.

sessionStatusHistoryStopTime.name: sessionStatusHistoryStopTime
sessionStatusHistoryStopTime.description: The time that this session stopped, in seconds since the system booted. This variable is only meaningful for sessions having the state inactive(0).

sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfModemSync.name: sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfModemSync
sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfModemSync.description: The time at which the modem synchronization completed, in seconds since the system booted.

sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfService.name: sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfService
sessionStatusHistoryTimeOfService.description: The time that this session entered its first negotiated or configured service, in seconds since the system booted. For example, for a session with serviceMode PPP, the time at which LCP and IPCP negotiations completed and the session was ready to forward user data.

sessionStatusHistoryTerminatingComponent.name: sessionStatusHistoryTerminatingComponent
sessionStatusHistoryTerminatingComponent.description: The component which initiated termination of this session. In cases where there are multiple causes of session termination, only the first cause detected is reported. This variable is only meaningful for sessions having the state inactive(0).

sessionStatusHistoryTerminationCause.name: sessionStatusHistoryTerminationCause

sessionStatusHistoryLinkCount.name: sessionStatusHistoryLinkCount
sessionStatusHistoryLinkCount.description: The number of sessions sharing the same remote IP address as this session. After a session is terminated, this value will represent the number of sessions at the time of termination.

sessionStatusHistoryTxStartDataRate.name: sessionStatusHistoryTxStartDataRate
sessionStatusHistoryTxStartDataRate.description: The transmit DCE data rate for this session. In the case of modem sessions, this will be the DCE rate reported as a result of initial modem negotiation, and may not track rate chanes during the call. For ISDN sessions, this will be the actual data service rate of the call. For Frame Relay sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the Frame Relay Physical Interface, even though multiple sessions may be sharing that Physical Interface. For other sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the physical interface. In no case should this be interepreted as a Quality-of-Service guarantee, or as the current line utilization or effective bandwidth on the interface. Note also that in the case of PPP multilink, this specifies the rate of only this link in the bundle, and not the aggregate rate of all links in the bundle.

sessionStatusHistoryRxStartDataRate.name: sessionStatusHistoryRxStartDataRate
sessionStatusHistoryRxStartDataRate.description: The receive data rate for this session. In the case of modem sessions, this will be the DCE rate reported as a result of initial modem negotiation, and may not track rate chanes during the call. For ISDN sessions, this will be the actual data service rate of the call. For Frame Relay sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the Frame Relay Physical Interface, even though multiple sessions may be sharing that Physical Interface. For other sessions, this will be the nominal speed of the physical interface. In no case should this be interepreted as a Quality-of-Service guarantee, or as the current line utilization or effective bandwidth on the interface. Note also that in the case of PPP multilink, this specifies the rate of only this link in the bundle, and not the aggregate rate of all links in the bundle.

sessionStatusHistoryRxEndDataRate.name: sessionStatusHistoryRxEndDataRate

sessionStatusHistoryRxMinDataRate.name: sessionStatusHistoryRxMinDataRate
sessionStatusHistoryRxMinDataRate.description: The minimum receive data rate during a modem session.

sessionStatusHistoryRxMaxDataRate.name: sessionStatusHistoryRxMaxDataRate

sessionStatusHistoryTandemTimeslot.description: The timeslot used for the outbound portion of a tandem call, if applicable.

sessionStatusHistoryCallClassLen.description: The number of octets in callClassArray.

sessionStatusHistoryActualAuthMethod.name: sessionStatusHistoryActualAuthMethod
sessionStatusHistoryActualAuthMethod.description: The actual authentication method which was used to gain access to services. Radius, Local, Remote.

sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPXNetwork.description: The IPX network assigned to the dial-up user.

sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPXNode.name: sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPXNode
sessionStatusHistoryRemoteIPXNode.description: The IPX Node number assisgned to the dial-up user

slotStatusTable.name: slotStatusTable
slotStatusTable.description: This table describes the status of the physical slots in a CVX switch. NOTE: cards in the CVX chassis report two card types per slot. The Service Module is the main logic board, residing in the 'front' of the slot. The Line Termination Module, residing in the 'back' of the slot, houses the data and power connectors for the system.
